        "id": 1072905
      },
      "writtenOn": "2025-12-23T16:10:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e If there were files owned by FRONTEND_FILES_OWNER and there are no files owned by FRONTEND_FILES_OWNER in the new PS, shouldn\u0027t we keep the vote?\n\nThis is the case of a removal, which covered by `shouldNotCopyApprovalWhenOwnedFileIsDeleted` asserting the label is NOT copied over since the set of files owned by the user has changed.\n\nIn this test, we are asserting that if there are no files owned by the approver, then her vote should not be copied over, since in this context, she is not an owner.",
      "parentUuid": "ed0da48d_6697094b",
